misconceptions.student_thought_process: The student believes that the 'not found' case (represented by the sentinel value -1) must be handled as a separate logical branch with a literal string, rather than trusting the variable to be appended to the string template like any other index value.
misconceptions.conceptual_gap: The student fails to realize that string concatenation in Java (`"string" + var`) handles all primitive values, including negative integers, uniformly. They treat the '-1' state as a special exception that requires its own explicit print statement, even though the resulting output format is identical to the success case.
